                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ŋʰooɡ</pron>
                <pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">khuk</pron>
            </form>
            <def>Kū 哭 (ant. xiào 笑 "laugh with joy") is often used as a generalised verb referring to participation in all sorts of mourning rituals and activities.
</def>
<sense xml:id="uuid-457c2cf0-c67d-4dc5-b9a1-d02bc0f13c59">
<gramGrp>
                    <pos>V</pos>
  <tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-fbfb2371-2537-4a99-a876-41b15ec2463c">vtoN</tls:syn-func>
                    <usg type="warring-states-currency">4</usg>
                </gramGrp>
  <def>mourn (a person, mainly, but not only through demonstrative lamentation)</def>
            </sense>
</entry>
